hopobject.body: About a year womenshealthspecialists.net The article shows a breathtaking lack of understanding of ecology. One example: "bats feed mostly on moths, and less than 2% of their gut content is mosquitoes." That's like saying rice is unimportant in the human diet, based on a sample of visitors to a burger joint. There are around 1000 species of insect-eating bats, and mosquitoes, given their abundance, are almost certainly a significant component of the diets of many.
